J-K: Encounter underway between security forces, militants in Pulwama district 
17-3-2017 
An encounter has broken out between militants and security forces in Pulwama district. (Express Photo by Shuaib Masoodi) An encounter has broken out between militants and security forces in Pulwama district. (Express Photo by Shuaib Masoodi)

An encounter broke out between security forces and militants in Pulwama district of Jammu and Kashmir on Friday, according to police. According to news agency ANI, the area has been cordoned off by defence personnel as the militants have fled from the spot. This comes two days after a clash between the ultras and security forces in north Kashmir’s Kupwara district had killed three militants and a minor girl.

